text: You call this one thai basil pork rice? Sweet basil mostly use for green curry. If you donâ€™t know how to cook thai food please sell other things not thai food. Donâ€™t misuse THAI word. First and last time.
First time trying food from Nagara Thai. I must say I was a little skeptical at first but it all turned out good, well, at least what I've ordered turned out good.

First try for this stall.  Ordered seafood tom yum clear soup with rice set at $8.  Honestly ingredients is fresh but soup base cannot make it. First taste was sweet, then followed by extreme sourness with spicy, that's awful. Very hard to swallow. The soup base ruined this whole meal.
The mama noodle and basil chicken are spicy but delicious. Need to wait a bit since the business is good.

Regretted not taking a photo but WOW the honey chicken rice is damn good! Itâ€™s so hard to find such standards in thai restaurants these days. The sauce was just right, chicken was extremely crispy and fresh! Iâ€™ve eaten many honey chicken dishes from famous eateries in SG and have not found one which was as crispy as this. Kudos to the chef and staff! They were a friendly trio ðŸ˜Š will be back again with photos!
